{\bf x}=(x_1,\ldots,x_n)\in\mathbb{R}^n
\Vert A\Vert_1\leq\sqrt{m}\Vert A\Vert_2
\eqalignno{ \Vert A\,{\bf x}\Vert_1&=\sum_{i=1}^m\left\vert\sum_{j=1}^na_{ij}x_j\right\vert\cr &\leq \sum_{i=1}^m\sqrt{\sum_{j=1}^na_{ij}^2}\cdot\Vert {\bf x}\Vert_2&\hbox{by Cauchy-Schwarz}\cr &\leq\Vert {\bf x}\Vert_2\sqrt{m}\cdot \sqrt{\sum_{i=1}^m\sum_{j=1}^na_{ij}^2}&\hbox{again by Cauchy-Schwarz}\cr &=\sqrt{m}\Vert A\Vert_2 \Vert {\bf x}\Vert_2\cr &\leq\sqrt{m}\Vert A\Vert_2 \Vert {\bf x}\Vert_1&(*)\cr } 
 \left(\sum_{j=1}^n|x_j|^2\right)^{1/2}\leq\sum_{j=1}^n|x_j| 
